Barn : Birgitta f. 35, Monica 38. — Stud:ex. i Norrköp. 13i fil. mag. i Upps. 21, provår i Sthlm 26. E. o. ämneslär. v. Gästrikl. folkhögsk. 21-23’ i Lindesberg 23-24, vik. adj. i Gävle 24-25, i Åmål 25-26, vik. lektor v. Luleå folksk:sem. 27-28, vik. adj. v. norra latin i Sthlm 28-36, adj. i hist. m. samh :lära o. geogr. v. Vänersb. h. a. 1. sed. 36. Res. t. translated: Åberg, Fredrik Emanuel, high school teacher, Vänersborg, born on January 1, 1895 in Österåker, Södermanland County. Son of parish priest Edvard A. and his wife, formerly d’0’rchimont. Married to Svea Johansson since 1927. Children: Birgitta born in 1935, Monica in 1938. Completed secondary school examination in Norrköping in 1913, received a Bachelor's degree in Philosophy at Uppsala University in 1921, and completed a probationary year in Stockholm in 1926. Assistant teacher at Gästrikland Folk High School from 1921-1923, Lindesberg from 1923-1924, temporary teacher in Gävle from 1924-1925, Åmål from 1925-1926, temporary lecturer at Luleå Teacher Training College from 1927-1928, temporary assistant at Norra Latin School in Stockholm from 1928-1936. Teacher of history, social studies, and geography at Vänersborg high school from 1936. Travelled to Germany, Austria, and Switzerland in 1922, London in 1924, Rome (member of the Swedish Archaeological Institute), France, and Germany in 1927.
